### Create an academy
POST http://localhost:8080/api/academies
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bright Minds Academy",
  "slug": "bright-minds"
}

### List all academies
GET http://localhost:8080/api/academies

### Get one academy (use an id that exists)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/academies/1

### Update an academy
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/academies/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bright Minds Tutoring"
}

### Create a course under that academy (set academyId to a real id)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/courses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "academyId": 1,
  "title": "SAT Math - Fall 2026",
  "subject": "Mathematics",
  "term": "Fall 2026"
}

### List all courses
GET http://localhost:8080/api/courses

### List courses for one academy only
GET http://localhost:8080/api/courses?academyId=1

### Get one course
GET http://localhost:8080/api/courses/1

### Update a course
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/courses/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "SAT Math (Advanced) - Fall 2026",
  "subject": "Mathematics",
  "term": "Fall 2026"
}

### Delete a course
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/courses/1

### --- Error cases to see the exception handler in action ---

### 400: validation failure (blank name, bad slug)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/academies
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "slug": "Bad Slug!"
}

### 404: academy that doesn't exist
GET http://localhost:8080/api/academies/9999

### 409: duplicate slug (run the first create twice)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/academies
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Another Academy",
  "slug": "bright-minds"
}